'''伊查姆湖'''（{{lang-en|Lake Eacham}}，读作{{lang|en|Yeetcham}}；<ref>{{Cite web|title=Lake Eacham|url=https://www.dnrme.qld.gov.au/qld/environment/land/place-names/search#/search=Lake_Eacham&types=0&place=Lake_Eacham10992|accessdate=2021-02-14|work=Queensland place names search|publisher=Queensland Government|archive-date=2020-10-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201006162152/https://www.dnrme.qld.gov.au/qld/environment/land/place-names/search#/search=Lake_Eacham&types=0&place=Lake_Eacham10992|dead-url=no}}</ref>原名为{{lang|en|Yidyam}}或{{lang|en|Wiinggina}}<ref name="NgEaWeb">[http://earthsci.org/aboriginal/Ngadjonji%20History/antquity/history2.htm  Ngadjonji - Earthwatch web page.] {{Wayback|url=http://earthsci.org/aboriginal/Ngadjonji%20History/antquity/history2.htm |date=20080202233604 }} Accessed 5 November 2007.</ref>）坐落于澳洲[[昆士兰州|昆士兰州]]的[[阿瑟顿高原|阿瑟顿高原]]，是十分受欢迎的[[火山湖|火山湖]]，位于[[世界遗产名录|世界遗产名录]]中的[[昆士兰湿热带地区|昆士兰湿热带地区]]。

==起源==
雅伊查姆湖森湖和邻近的[[巴灵顿湖|巴灵顿湖]]在大约12,000年前由熔岩浆形成。[[岩浆|岩浆]]从地心升到[[地表|地表]]，加热[[地下水|地下水]]。沸水产生的[[蒸汽|蒸汽]]被困在地下，直到大规模[[爆发|爆发]]。地面出现巨大的裂缝，使曾经布满山边的大树被夷平烧毁。过了几百年，水逐渐注满[[火山口|火山口]]，大树再次生长，形成了今天这一平静的湖，让家庭和游客可以在岸边[[消遣|消遣]]。没有任何溪流流入或流出伊查姆湖，湖水只通过渗透和蒸发流失，只通过雨水补充，水位在湿季和旱季之间的涨落可达4米<ref name="nprsra">{{cite web |url=http://www.nprsr.qld.gov.au/parks/lake-eacham/index.html |title=Lake Eacham, Crater Lakes National Park |author= |date=2012-10-17 |publisher=Department of National Parks, Recreation, Sport and Racing |accessdate=2012-12-29 |archive-date=2016-05-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160516002549/http://www.nprsr.qld.gov.au/parks/lake-eacham/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。 

